isc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"four original tenets ofhip-hop\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 857}, {\"ngram\": \"graffiti\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"rapping\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 896}, {\"ngram\": \"crews\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 916}, {\"ngram\": \"acrobatic dance moves\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 969}, {\"ngram\": \"a backdrop\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 984}, {\"ngram\": \"DJ beats\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 996}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As its popularity surged, breaking became represented by a series of international events and competitions, culminating in its inclusion, to widespread acclaim, on the programme for the 2018 Youth Olympic Games in Buenos Aires.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buenos_Aires\", \"score\": 0.9999996177342203, \"rank\": 3.278312309204098e-07, \"text\": \"Buenos Aires\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buenos_Aires\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buenos_Aires\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its popularity\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1015}, {\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"international events\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1087}, {\"ngram\": \"competitions\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1104}, {\"ngram\": \"its inclusion\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1134}, {\"ngram\": \"widespread acclaim\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"the programme\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1175}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2018 Youth Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1208}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both men's and women's eventsin Paris comprise 16 b-boys or b-girls, drawn into four groups of four.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1259, \"end\": 1264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999469992, \"rank\": 5.299499908863911e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Both men's and women's eventsin\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1258}, {\"ngram\": \"16 b-boys\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1283}, {\"ngram\": \"b-girls\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1294}, {\"ngram\": \"four groups\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1318}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They face off against other in an initial round-robin phase, with the two group winners advancing to straight knock-outs from the quarter-finals onwards.\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1481, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an initial round-robin phase\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1387}, {\"ngram\": \"the two group winners\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"straight knock-outs\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1448}, {\"ngram\": \"the quarter-finals\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1472}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each competitor performs solo, to music of the DJ's choosing, with each of three rounds consisting of six alternating one-minute segments.\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1529, \"end\": 1531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 0.9825975693644587, \"rank\": 0.0177106387988254, \"text\": \"DJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each competitor\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"three rounds\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"six alternating one-minute segments\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1619}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each round is scored by a panel of judges based on technique, vocabulary, execution, musicality and originality.\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each round\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1631}, {\"ngram\":